note:

<SGDescription:\fs[14] Sender: yari_man@dokage_maga.com Title: [Lizard

Thank you for your continued support. I am in charge of
human resources at Lizard Magazine. I would like to inform
you about a matter concerning Saki-sama that occurred during
the wrap-up party after our recent photo shoot. According to
our investigation, Saki-sama's collapse was merely due to
excessive drinking, and the atmosphere was no different from
our usual wrap-up parties. Of course, our company also bears
responsibility for not being able to manage the temporary

apologies once again. We hope that this incident will not

name:
\fs[14]project_pregnancy@inmalabo.com
\fs[18] \V[291]
note:
<SGCategory:研究機関>
<SGDescription:\fs[14] Sender: project_pregnancy@inmalabo.com Title: About
the recruitment for clinical trials of the new project at
InmaLabo \fs[22] We appreciate your continued support. I am
the leader of the research team. I have been assigned to a
new project this time. There was an issue with subjects
resisting during the experiments, but as you introduced to
us the other day, the research institution's opinion is that
they were durable and had good sensitivity, making them
excellent clinical subjects. We will send you separate
information and recruitment requirements for the next
clinical trial, so please check and respond accordingly.
There are many items related to this experiment's results,
so we would like to proceed with the same subjects if
possible.>

name:
\fs[14]project_pregnancy@inmalabo.com
\fs[18] \V[292]
note:
<SGCategory:研究機関>
<SGDescription:\fs[14] Sender: project_pregnancy@inmalabo.com Title:
[InmaLabo] Regarding the content of clinical experiments and
request for the next experimental subject \fs[22] We are
sending you the documents related to this experiment and
future experiments. We will also send you the schedule for
the next session and the attendance records of the temporary
staff. As the durability and sensitivity continue to show
excellent indicators, we intend to continue requesting
superb clinical subjects. However, we ask that you pay close
attention to hygiene management after the experiments, as it
is a place where precise experimental results are collected.
We now require more experimental results, so in addition to
the subjects of this experiment, we would like to introduce
various other potential groups. We will send the related
matters separately, so we would appreciate it if you could
confirm and respond promptly.>

name:
\fs[14]project_pregnancy@inmalabo.com
\fs[18] \V[293]
note:
<SGCategory:研究機関>
<SGDescription:\fs[14] Sender: project_pregnancy@inmalabo.com Title:
[InmaLabo] Dispatch of Documents and Precautions Regarding
Dispatch \fs[22] We are sending you the schedule for the
next session along with related precautions. The experiments
are progressing smoothly, however, there is a tendency for
the clinical subjects to reject our facility, so we ask for
your cooperation in providing a steady supply of
experimental subjects. Please be aware that such aggressive
behavior towards our staff may adversely affect your
company's evaluation. We have attached documents concerning
the next experiment, so please check them.>

name:
\fs[14]project_pregnancy@inmalabo.com

note:

[InmaLabo] Regarding the delivery of content for future

plans. Thanks to your cooperation, this experiment has come
to an end. We will contact you as soon as the schedule for
future clinical trials is determined. Thank you very much
for your cooperation. We look forward to your continued
support.>

description:
The article details the series of disappearances
involving succubi. There are no commonalities
among the victims, and five have vanished over the
course of two months. Whether it's a planned crime
or a mere coincidence remains a question as the
incident gradually fades into obscurity...
name: Article on the Mysterious Series of Disappearances

description:
This media guideline serves as the foundation to
grant high value to the succubus industry as a new
renewable energy source and to garner full support
from the general populace as a future national
industry. The published guidelines do not appear
to be intentionally damaged...
name: Succubus First Industry Media Guidelines

description:
These are fragments of documents that were found
shredded in the trash can, marked with a
distinctive pattern.
name: Torn Documents

description:
A draft article about the death of a client who
used the services of the succubus industry. It
coincides with the issuance of the media
guidelines and seems to have been rejected for
publication. Despite the date being quite old, it
was found tucked away in a drawer corner. It is
written that the client died from having their
life force drained excessively during sexual
intercourse.
name: Article on the Death of a Client Using Succubus First Industry Services

description:
A document entrusted by an employee of a logistics

not be opened...

a research institution. It's so customized to
one's body that it gives goosebumps...

description:
A report found at a research institution. It
suggests that the more succubi become dependent on
vital energy, the more they also become dependent
on men. This is thought to be because succubi have
historically been used as consumables.
